  "chunk_index": 34,
  "summary": "George Romax examines the coded letters found by Anthony on a dressing table. Chief Constable Bartle reports that Kidd’s background has been partially verified via a telegram from South Africa, confirming he worked for the Joice Travels agency in Bulawayo with a Mr. McGrath. Suspecting Kidd's motives, George urges the immediate decoding of the letters and suggests contacting Professor Wood, a former British Museum department head and specialist, to assist. Bartle notes that a telegram has already been sent to arrange Wood's arrival by train.\n\nAs George prepares to depart for London, he requests that Bill Everly be summoned to the monastery once George has left. Bartle shares a theory that \"King Victor the Deceiver\" may have returned the letters to cause trouble and misdirect investigators away from the hiding place of certain diamonds.\n\nWhile driving Anthony back to the villa, Bartle reveals that a handgun was discovered in Esakistan's suitcase, a finding Bartle believes aligns with his theories. Anthony is tasked with locating Everly, whom he spots walking with Mrs. Ruff. Later, Anthony speaks with Virginia Rue regarding his previous investigations into Miss White and the Countess de Bredouille de Dinard. Their conversation is interrupted by Boris, a Hesslovac servant, who is watching them. Boris approaches Anthony and hands him a torn piece of paper containing a messy, handwritten address, claiming it was dropped by a \"foreign gentleman.\"",
